&gt; (1) is what you do when you&#39;re extending an API, i.e. A knows about B
&gt; but B doesn&#39;t know about A; 
&gt; 
&gt; (2) or (3) is what you do when A and B are defined as part of the same
&gt; API, i.e. they know about each other;
&gt; 
&gt; (4) is how you unify two unrelated APIs, i.e. neither A nor B knows
